     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'image_url': 'https://img.freepik.com/premium-photo/red-kidney-bean-is-variety-common-bean-wooden-bowl-phaseolus-vulgaris-jogo_717054-259.jpg',\n",
       " 'caption': 'This image showcases a detailed, aesthetic, top-down view of a wooden bowl filled to the brim with approximately one or two cups of dry pinto beans. The bowl, perfectly centered on a wooden table, emphasizes the rustic simplicity of the scene. The beans themselves are predominantly light brown with darker red splotches and speckles, each displaying unique patterns and textures, including small, distinct white eyes. The close-up perspective captures the intricate details and variety in color, making the beans appear almost like a cross between beans and peanuts. The overall composition highlights the natural beauty and texture of the dry beans against the blurred, wooden background.',\n",
       " 'transcripts': [\"So this is a picture of a bowl of beans, so the picture looks like it's taken on a wooden table and the beans are inside of a circular wooden bowl. The beans, they are kind of light brown in color. Some of them are darker, but most of them are light brown with darker red splotches on them. There's a good number of beans, maybe like 40 of them that you can see. The bowl of the beans is just perfectly centered in the middle of the picture and there's not really anything else going on. It just kind of looks like an aesthetic type photo.\",\n",
       "  \"So this is an up-close image of beans. They're dry beans. It looks like maybe pinto beans. They are kind of all just piled up. They have kind of a cool like pattern to them. They're not just like one flat color. They've got little speckles of like a darker tone of the kind of reddish brown that they are. And then all of these beans, it's maybe like a cup or two of beans, and they're all in a wooden bowl. And it's just a plain wooden bowl sitting on top of a wooden table. Not a whole lot going on beyond that. The beans are dry. You can kind of see the little eyes of the beans and all the different texture to them. And they're just beans.\",\n",
       "  \"So this looks to be a photo of some sort of a top-down view of some sort of brown sort of beans. So you see a brown like wood counter in the background that's blurred. Then on this you're looking top-down and what looks to be a wooden bowl. It's a very thick sort of wooden ring and in this stacked up quite densely and quite high is a bunch of beans. They look very dry and they almost look like a mix between beans and peanuts in a way. They're red and orangish. They're all different. They all have sort of speckled scattered sort of patterns on them. They all have little white dots at the bottom of them. They look almost like a sort of red bean and this is a very close-up photo of these.\"]}"
